The solution consists of two helper methods: findLeftIndex and findRightIndex. The findLeftIndex method iterates through the array from the end to the beginning, checking if each element is less than the pivot. If an element is found, the right index is updated. The findRightIndex method does the same but iterates from the beginning to the end and updates the left index if an element is found greater than the pivot. Finally, the main method returns the resultant array by iterating from the left index to the right index and copying the elements to the result array. The time complexity is O(n), where n is the length of the input array. The space complexity is O(1), as we only use a single array to store the result. The energy implications are low, as the solution only involves simple array operations and does not require any energy-consuming operations.

